  &lt;p id="Ha1yYx"&gt;Somebody goofed — and now AMD’s unannounced Ryzen 9000X3D desktop processors have been partially revealed. But &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/10/24265928/intel-core-ultra-200s-series-specs-release-date-pricing"&gt;like Intel’s new Arrow Lake desktop CPUs&lt;/a&gt;, it doesn’t look like they’ll be a huge performance improvement on their predecessors. If so, that’s a shame given &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/14/24220250/amd-zen-5-cpu-reviews-ryzen-9-9950x"&gt;how poorly received AMD’s Ryzen 9000 was&lt;/a&gt;, to begin with.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id="yJZQxC"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="gallery:12450692"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="gUcSVu"&gt;According to slides from an MSI presentation &lt;a href="https://www.hardwareluxx.de/index.php/artikel/hardware/mainboards/64582-msi-factory-tour-in-shenzhen-wie-ein-mainboard-das-licht-der-welt-erblickt.html"&gt;published by &lt;em&gt;HardwareLuxx&lt;/em&gt; today&lt;/a&gt; (via &lt;a href="https://videocardz.com/newz/msi-leaks-ryzen-9000x3d-2-to-13-higher-gaming-performance-than-7000x3d"&gt;&lt;em&gt;VideoCardz&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), the new chips may have respectable multicore performance gen-over-gen, with an eight-core 9000X3D outperforming a Ryzen 7 7900X3D by up to 28 percent in Cinebench R23. But they can offer as little as 2 percent gains in &lt;em&gt;Black Myth: Wukong&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Shadow of the Tomb Raider&lt;/em&gt;, according to MSI’s preliminary testing. &lt;/p&gt;
