    <title>Casio made a furry robot designed to cuddle and calm you down</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="A person pets the top of Casio’s Moflin robotic pet." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SmgeJQNxfM56EYKahEVuNXgRb1Y=/0x1:1275x851/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73648026/moflin1.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;Unlike Sony’s robotic dog, Aibo, Casio’s Moflin can’t run away on its own.&lt;/em&gt; | Image: Casio&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="rfha9x"&gt;Casio has opened preorders for its &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casio.com%2Fjp%2Fmoflin%2F&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F10%2F11%2F24268063%2Fcasio-robot-pet-moflin" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;robotic pet called Moflin&lt;/a&gt; that looks like a cross between a hamster and &lt;em&gt;Star Trek&lt;/em&gt;’s Tribbles. Unlike &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2018/1/11/16876086/sony-aibo-hands-on-video-ces-2018"&gt;Sony’s robot dog Aibo&lt;/a&gt; that can follow you around, Moflin is designed to be held and cuddled, and over time, Casio says it will learn who you are and attempt to develop a simulated bond expressed through unique sounds and movements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="kAtlhW"&gt;Originally developed through a collaboration with a Japanese startup called &lt;a href="https://ces.vporoom.com/VanguardIndustries/Japanese-Hardware-Startup-Vanguard-Industries-Inc-Honored-With-Best-of-Innovation-Awards-From-CES-2021"&gt;Vanguard Industries&lt;/a&gt;, Moflin is now being manufactured and distributed by Casio. It can be &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casio.com%2Fjp%2Fmoflin%2Fproduct.PE-M10SR%2F&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F10%2F11%2F24268063%2Fcasio-robot-pet-moflin" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;preordered for ￥59,400&lt;/a&gt; (around $398 USD) and is expected to be available starting on November 7th. Casio is also offering an optional subscription service called Club Moflin for ￥6,600 (about $44 USD) per year,...&lt;/p&gt;
